applyAllowlistedWorkflowsUpdates.t.sol
├─ when the caller does not have the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
│  └─ it should revert
└─ when the caller has the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
   ├─ when both removes and adds are empty
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when either removes or adds are not empty
      ├─ when a removed workflow ID is not allowlisted
      │  └─ it should revert
      ├─ when an added workflow ID is zero
      │  └─ it should revert
      ├─ when only adding workflows
      │  ├─ it should allowlist the workflow IDs, targets, and selectors
      │  └─ it should emit the correct events
      ├─ when only removing workflows
      │  ├─ it should remove the workflow IDs from the allowlist
      │  ├─ it should clean up all targets and selectors for the removed workflows
      │  └─ it should emit the correct events
      └─ when adding and removing workflows in the same call
         ├─ it should process removes before adds
         └─ it should correctly reflect the final allowlisted state
